evidence.text: Stephan v. United States, 319 U.S. 423, 426 (1943) (per curiam); see also U.S. Nat’l Bank of Oregon v. Indep. Ins. Agents of Am., Inc., 508 U.S. 439, 448 (1993) ("[T]he Statutes at Large . . . provide[] the 'legal evidence of laws.'" (quoting 1 U.S.C. § 112)); Preston v. Heckler, 734 F.2d 1359, 1368 (9th Cir. 1984) (The law "as it appears in the Statutes at Large must prevail" over an "inconsistent" version in the United States Code).
